🔹 🎯 Task 2: Repeat a String
You are writing a text-formatting helper with two flavours: repeat a string N times, or repeat it with a separator.
📥 Input:
String word;
int    times;
String separator;
⚙️ Requirements:
•
Write repeat(String word, int times) → returns the word concatenated times times (no separator)
•
Write repeat(String word, int times, String separator) → returns the word joined times times using separator
•
Both methods must return a String, not print it
•
main prints the results of both calls
⚠️ Watch out:
•
Strings are immutable — building with + inside a loop creates a new object every iteration. For this task it's acceptable, but be aware the result of + is always a brand-new String.
•
Return type alone cannot distinguish overloads; only parameter list matters.
📤 Output format:
No separator: XXXX
With separator: X-X-X
📌 Test cases:
Input: word="ha", times=3, separator="-"
Output:
No separator: hahaha
With separator: ha-ha-ha

Input: word="go", times=1, separator=", "
Output:
No separator: go
With separator: go

Input: word="ab", times=4, separator="."
Output:
No separator: abababab
With separator: ab.ab.ab.ab

Input: word="!", times=2, separator=" "
Output:
No separator: !!
With separator: ! !

